item.title: CS26-lecture-notes
item.description: CS 26 Lecture Notes # Jan 28, 2019 # Introduction # Discrete: Not “discreet”, opposite of continuous, goes in steps. The graphs we worked with can only be expanded in steps, you can’t add a half edge or half vertex. Structure: a set of related values and the operations on them. (integers, graphs). Like a venn diagram of math and computer science, discrete structures is the combination.
